<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>29<percent/> of 246</li> 
<li>1<percent/> of 1810</li> 
<li>87<percent/> of 36</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>A: 29<percent/> of 246</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{87}\%\cdot{36}={31.32}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{29}\%\cdot{246}={71.34}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{1}\%\cdot{1810}={18.1}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 29<percent/> of 246 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

